Once, he tried cooking.

266
00:19:28,950 --> 00:19:31,810
He also tried building things with toy blocks and toy robots.

267
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:35,550
- Once... 
- He's just killing time, to sum up.

268
00:19:37,210 --> 00:19:38,920
What about writing?

269
00:19:39,310 --> 00:19:40,750
He's not writing.

270
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:43,710
- Not at all? 
- Not at all.

271
00:19:45,110 --> 00:19:46,650
Why is that?

272
00:20:09,950 --> 00:20:11,010
Se Ju.

273
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:14,420
Hi. You're here.

274
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:20,750
What are you doing now?

275
00:20:23,150 --> 00:20:24,480
"Carpe Diem".

276
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:27,650
What Diem?

277
00:20:28,950 --> 00:20:31,150
It means to enjoy the moment.

278
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:36,250
Live the very moment you are living right now.

279
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:40,780
I've been spending my time only writing in a room,

280
00:20:41,450 --> 00:20:44,710
so I couldn't enjoy my life.

281
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:47,650
Now I'm properly enjoying it.

282
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,110
What's wrong with you?

283
00:20:52,380 --> 00:20:55,050
(Mr. Kim's double life)

284
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:02,210
Why aren't you writing? You're a writer. You should write.

285
00:21:02,210 --> 00:21:03,650
Hey, look.

286
00:21:04,010 --> 00:21:06,010
Look at all the beautiful books.

287
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:09,750
Look at the writers who are immortal through books.

288
00:21:09,850 --> 00:21:12,050
How could you run away from such a beautiful world?

289
00:21:12,050 --> 00:21:15,210
- I told you I'm in a slump. 
- You've overcome it.

290
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:17,450
You already wrote the serial novel.

291
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:19,380
I told you already.

292
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:22,480
- My ghostwriter wrote the... 
- And the ghostwriter...

293
00:21:23,210 --> 00:21:25,310
is a real ghost, right?

294
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:31,080
I don't care even if you don't believe me.

295
00:21:33,010 --> 00:21:34,080
Se Ju.

296
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:37,550
Think about how hard it was to make it here.

297
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:38,750
Do you remember...

298
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:42,450
the day we met each other for the first time?

299
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:44,750
(8 years ago)

300
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:48,180
It was a sunny day in April.

301
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:52,080
It was a cloudy day in April.

302
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:53,580
Don't gloss over it.

303
00:21:56,380 --> 00:21:58,550
Gosh, I've been looking for you.

304
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:04,710
Move the backlight away. I told you it was cloudy that day.

305
00:22:04,710 --> 00:22:06,850
No, it was sunny.

306
00:22:08,210 --> 00:22:09,610
You're Han Se Ju, right?

307
00:22:12,550 --> 00:22:14,910
You were wearing a worn out sweatsuit.

308
00:22:16,450 --> 00:22:18,610
Your hair was parted at the rate of 2 to 8.

309
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:22,350
You look way better in real.

310
00:22:22,380 --> 00:22:24,480
I bet your books will be popular just for its writer being handsome.

311
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:26,950
Who are you?

312
00:22:26,950 --> 00:22:27,950
Me?

313
00:22:29,550 --> 00:22:32,650
I'm a dark horse in the publishing world...

314
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:35,950
who is going to make an ordinary amateur writer...

315
00:22:35,950 --> 00:22:38,750
Han Se Ju into a bestselling author.

316
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:44,810
Hey, young man. I'm not finished talking yet.

317
00:22:45,110 --> 00:22:47,450
Hey. Hey.

318
00:22:49,050 --> 00:22:50,810
Han Se Ju is an imitator of Baek Tae Min.

319
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:55,450
Han Se Ju's "Destiny" is nothing more than...

320
00:22:55,450 --> 00:22:57,180
an imitation of Baek Tae Min's "Fate".

321
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:07,480
Do you want to be eliminated in the literary world in Korea?

322
00:23:07,910 --> 00:23:11,910
Don't you want to get back at them who are saying you're an imitator?

323
00:23:12,580 --> 00:23:14,880
Is there any way to do that?

324
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:19,450
You don't look that successful though.

325
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:25,480
I'm going to found a publishing company soon.

326
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:29,050
I can give you the chance to write the first book to be published.

327
00:23:29,480 --> 00:23:32,380
But you might need to change the genre to more popular one.

328
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:35,480
- Why... 
- Why did I pick you?

329
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:40,150
As soon as I read your writing, I got the feeling.

330
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:42,180
Talent, character, and appearance.

331
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:45,110
You got all these three things. You're definitely going to...

332
00:23:45,110 --> 00:23:47,710
be a star writer. So I...

333
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:51,650
I mean we...

334
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:54,610
We are going to be incredibly rich.

335
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:56,850
What do you think?

336
00:23:57,750 --> 00:23:59,250
Do you want to join me or not?

337
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:00,580
I'd like to join you.

338
00:24:02,810 --> 00:24:03,810
Really?

339
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:06,280
Why?

340
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:08,910
You're cheesy and snob. And above all,

341
00:24:08,910 --> 00:24:11,880
I like that you are outrightly crazy about money.

342
00:24:11,880 --> 00:24:13,210
Don't ever change.

343
00:24:20,150 --> 00:24:22,180
That was us.

344
00:24:22,450 --> 00:24:24,550
I never change. Why do you change?

345
00:24:25,010 --> 00:24:27,410
How can your belief change so easily?

346
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:33,110
At the time, I had a clear goal.

347
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,880
It may have been impure, but I had a purpose.

348
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:38,310
- But how about now? 
- I have nothing.

349
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:43,010
I'm confused about everything.

350
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:48,980
Se Ju.

351
00:24:49,650 --> 00:24:52,610
What's confusing you? Tell me. I'll clarify it for you.

352
00:24:53,710 --> 00:24:55,710
I said everything is confusing.

353
00:24:56,380 --> 00:24:59,380
I don't know what I'm writing,

354
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:02,150
and I don't know why I need to write it.

355
00:25:02,380 --> 00:25:04,050
You can come up with reasons.

356
00:25:04,050 --> 00:25:06,710
Just stop a stranger and ask.

357
00:25:06,710 --> 00:25:09,710
See how many people know why they live. Everyone...

358
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:12,750
- Everyone lives like that. 
- More than anything,

359
00:25:14,310 --> 00:25:16,950
I am no longer happy when I write.

360
00:25:19,650 --> 00:25:21,550
What's wrong with you? You're acting like an amateur.

361
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:26,480
I'm too tired from writing something that's worth money.

362
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:28,950
I don't want to write anything...

363
00:25:29,910 --> 00:25:32,480
that doesn't make money even if it's writing a diary.

364
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:35,750
- And... 
- Why would you say "and"?

365
00:25:35,780 --> 00:25:37,180
It should be "but".

366
00:25:38,480 --> 00:25:39,810
And...

367
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:44,710
(I miss you more at night than in the afternoon.)

368
00:25:55,850 --> 00:25:59,610
I'm confused about the past and the present life.

369
00:26:00,910 --> 00:26:04,150
Did I really write that? Or didn't I?

370
00:26:05,010 --> 00:26:07,280
Is my heart stirred...

371
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,950
because of Su Hyeon from the past life?

372
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:11,610
Or is it because of...

373
00:26:11,780 --> 00:26:13,450
- He did really well. 
- He did?

374
00:26:14,810 --> 00:26:16,580
Good job.

375
00:26:17,180 --> 00:26:19,750
It's his first time to get vaccinated, so...

376
00:26:20,180 --> 00:26:22,680
Please watch him well.

377
00:26:23,710 --> 00:26:25,080
For a day, you shouldn't...

378
00:26:35,210 --> 00:26:36,310
Doctor?

379
00:26:37,810 --> 00:26:42,080
For a day, you shouldn't make him exercise or take him outside.

380
00:26:42,980 --> 00:26:44,580
I'll see you in two weeks.

381
00:27:20,350 --> 00:27:22,450
So he got kicked out from the hospital too.

382
00:27:22,910 --> 00:27:26,480
He wasn't kicked out. She has a point.

383
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:29,480
If people hear that we take in abandoned dogs,

384
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:32,150
more people will abandon their dogs in front of the clinic.

385
00:27:33,250 --> 00:27:35,850
Right. Why don't you ask Mr. Baek to take him?

386
00:27:36,010 --> 00:27:38,980
But it's too late. We're not that close.

387
00:27:40,310 --> 00:27:42,180
What do we do with him then?

388
00:27:45,750 --> 00:27:46,850
Welcome.

389
00:27:46,850 --> 00:27:50,350
The dog in front of the shop is yours, isn't he?

390
00:27:50,850 --> 00:27:52,550
No.

391
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:56,080
He's my friend's. They're leaving soon.

392
00:27:56,380 --> 00:27:59,180
I'm sorry. I'll take him right now.

393
00:28:03,310 --> 00:28:05,810
I'm sorry, Seol. I'll be done soon.

394
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:08,480
Take a stroll around this area. Okay?

395
00:28:15,050 --> 00:28:16,250
I'm sorry.

396
00:28:17,650 --> 00:28:18,680
About what?

397
00:28:19,410 --> 00:28:21,880
You got yelled at because of me.

398
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:24,710
Don't worry about it.

399
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:27,750
I'm sorry.

400
00:28:29,050 --> 00:28:30,680
About what again?

401
00:28:32,610 --> 00:28:35,280
I am already living off you, and I even brought a dog with me.

402
00:28:37,250 --> 00:28:40,010
I'm really sorry to you,

403
00:28:40,950 --> 00:28:43,550
but Gyun Woo reminds me of my old self.

404
00:28:43,850 --> 00:28:45,550
So I can't neglect him.

405
00:28:50,410 --> 00:28:53,180
When my dad passed away and I became alone,

406
00:28:55,580 --> 00:29:00,050
I had nowhere to go and your mom took me in.

407
00:29:01,350 --> 00:29:04,650
If you and your mom didn't take me in,

408
00:29:05,550 --> 00:29:08,080
I would've wandered around like Gyun Woo too.

409
00:29:15,550 --> 00:29:18,250
Why are you crying? You're embarrassing me.

410
00:29:18,550 --> 00:29:20,580
Why are you so sorry all the time?

411
00:29:21,650 --> 00:29:25,280
When the kids didn't play with me because my mom's a shaman,

412
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:27,780
you were the only one that played with me.

413
00:29:27,910 --> 00:29:31,550
You fought for me and always sided with me.

414
00:29:32,010 --> 00:29:35,780
I felt so reassured because of you.

415
00:29:36,780 --> 00:29:38,710
I am the one with the sad story.

416
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:41,910
Why are you the one crying?

417
00:29:48,650 --> 00:29:50,780
Why are you crying and chasing away your luck?

418
00:29:55,610 --> 00:29:56,680
What are you doing?

419
00:30:00,980 --> 00:30:02,310
Whose tail is that?

420
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:12,680
Did you say he's not a Sapsali?

421
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:14,880
- No. He's an English Sheepdog. 
- He's an English Sheepdog.

422
00:30:23,710 --> 00:30:25,750
He's obviously a Sapsali.

423
00:30:25,780 --> 00:30:27,250
- He's not a Sapsali. 
- He's not a Sapsali.

424
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:29,210
If he's not a Sapsali,

425
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:31,810
I don't need him.

426
00:30:32,210 --> 00:30:33,210
- He's a Sapsali. 
- He's a Sapsali.

427
00:30:33,210 --> 00:30:36,310
How dare you lie to me? Idiots.

428
00:30:36,310 --> 00:30:39,780
It's just a rumor that a Sapsali chases ghosts away.

429
00:30:39,950 --> 00:30:42,880
Look at him. He's so gentle. He can't chase ghosts away.

430
00:30:43,150 --> 00:30:46,580
He won't affect your business at all. Don't worry.

431
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:49,810
For now,

432
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:54,010
tie him over there.

433
00:30:56,180 --> 00:30:58,350
Really? Can I really do that?

434
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:02,250
If my business fails, it's all your fault, girl.

435
00:31:02,950 --> 00:31:05,780
Why am I the one getting blamed? Am I chasing the ghosts away?

436
00:31:08,110 --> 00:31:10,850
Welcome. Are you here to get your fortune told?

437
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:15,480
Goodness.

438
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:19,080
I'm keeping him so that the ghosts won't get to you.

439
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:21,480
How is it my fault?

440
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:25,880
I heard dogs these days don't eat scraps.

441
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:29,480
Seol, you will pay for his food.

442
00:31:29,810 --> 00:31:32,350
Of course. Thank you.

443
00:31:32,350 --> 00:31:35,810
- Tell me. Why is it my fault? 
- Things worked out well, right?

444
00:31:36,210 --> 00:31:39,480
You have to be a good boy, so she can love you.

445
00:31:39,610 --> 00:31:40,710
Okay?

446
00:32:07,980 --> 00:32:09,750
This is driving me crazy.

447
00:32:09,950 --> 00:32:12,250
Why is that dog so loud?

448
00:32:12,650 --> 00:32:15,380
He's going to bark all night.

449
00:32:15,780 --> 00:32:16,780
Goodness.

450
00:32:17,950 --> 00:32:20,250
It's because he's not used to this house.

451
00:32:20,450 --> 00:32:21,780
After today...

452
00:32:29,110 --> 00:32:31,680
Jeon Seol.

453
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:48,010
What's wrong?

454
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:57,780
I'm not going to abandon you.

455
00:32:58,010 --> 00:33:00,350
I'm going to find you good parents.

456
00:33:05,210 --> 00:33:07,250
Why did you cry so much?

457
00:33:07,780 --> 00:33:09,480
Did you cry because you were reminded of the past?

458
00:33:10,350 --> 00:33:13,410
Don't do that. Okay? It's better to forget sad memories fast.

459
00:33:13,580 --> 00:33:16,380
Look at me. I'm living just fine.

460
00:33:20,150 --> 00:33:23,110
Anyway, where should I send you?

461
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:45,350
(To Han Se Ju)

462
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:59,080
(Literature Camp)

463
00:33:59,780 --> 00:34:01,380
Han Se Ju is Baek Tae Min's imitator.

464
00:34:01,750 --> 00:34:04,910
Do you want to be eliminated in the literary world in Korea?

465
00:34:16,780 --> 00:34:18,080
Hello, Mr. Baek.

466
00:34:18,580 --> 00:34:22,210
I'm actually calling to ask a favor.

467
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:25,580
The other day, you said you'd look after Gyun Woo.

468
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:27,780
Is that offer still valid?

469
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,580
Really?

470
00:34:31,580 --> 00:34:33,280
Would you adopt him?

471
00:34:34,780 --> 00:34:37,380
Gosh, thank you. Thank you so much.

472
00:34:37,580 --> 00:34:39,950
- Then I'll go to your studio... 
- It's okay.

473
00:34:40,050 --> 00:34:43,050
I was just about to step out for a cup of coffee anyway.

474
00:34:43,180 --> 00:34:44,580
We might miss each other, so...

475
00:34:44,680 --> 00:34:46,980
I'll bring you coffee to thank you.

476
00:34:48,450 --> 00:34:49,680
Will you?

477
00:34:50,680 --> 00:34:53,580
What should I get? What do you usually drink?

478
00:35:05,980 --> 00:35:07,680
Let's have a quick talk.

479
00:35:08,450 --> 00:35:10,480
Two regular-sized Americano, please.

480
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:12,080
It's okay. I already got my coffee.

481
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,320
An extra shot in one of them, please.

482
00:35:15,080 --> 00:35:16,650
I already got my coffee with an extra shot.

483
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:18,950
They're to go, so I'd like a tray too.

484
00:35:19,010 --> 00:35:21,450
I'll let you know when they're ready.

485
00:35:21,550 --> 00:35:22,580
Thank you.

486
00:35:24,450 --> 00:35:27,080
Hey, am I invisible to you?

487
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:30,880
Why would you be invisible? You're perfectly visible.

488
00:35:32,110 --> 00:35:34,280
Why are you talking so casually to me though?

489
00:35:35,210 --> 00:35:38,980
I'd be polite to you if you were still the writer I admire,

490
00:35:39,050 --> 00:35:40,950
but I no longer have any reason to be like that.

491
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:43,080
It's about time we nail it down.

492
00:35:43,180 --> 00:35:44,880
If you talk politely to me, I'll do the same.

493
00:35:45,010 --> 00:35:46,750
If you talk casually, I'll talk to you the same way.

494
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:53,480
Anyway, let's talk first.

495
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:56,680
I guess I didn't make it simple enough for you.

496
00:35:56,680 --> 00:35:59,450
Will you keep talking casually to me or be polite with me?

497
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,080
- Look. 
- What?

498
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,910
Shall I be short with you too?

499
00:36:06,850 --> 00:36:10,180
I would like to talk to you about something.

500
00:36:17,180 --> 00:36:20,320
About the last time, I...

501
00:36:24,950 --> 00:36:26,380
I apologize.

502
00:36:29,680 --> 00:36:31,780
But if you know everything that happened,

503
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:35,080
you'd agree that it wasn't entirely my fault.

504
00:36:35,180 --> 00:36:38,580
I fully understand why you got the wrong idea,

505
00:36:39,210 --> 00:36:40,750
but I... I mean,

506
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:43,380
I don't abuse animals.

507
00:36:44,210 --> 00:36:47,480
Ripping your purse wasn't my doing.

508
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:51,880
There was also a reason I had to yell at you like that...

509
00:36:51,980 --> 00:36:53,580
Then who did it?

510
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:57,010
You won't believe me even if I tell you.

511
00:36:57,210 --> 00:36:59,820
I'll believe you. Please tell me.

512
00:37:04,820 --> 00:37:06,780
Do you believe in supernatural beings?

513
00:37:06,910 --> 00:37:08,650
Like ghosts, for example.

514
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:15,380
You'll find it hard to believe,

515
00:37:15,580 --> 00:37:17,950
but a third party intervened...

516
00:37:18,080 --> 00:37:20,880
between you and me.

517
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:25,880
- That person is... 
- Hey, Han Se Ju.

518
00:37:27,750 --> 00:37:29,580
What is the matter with you?

519
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:32,110
I've been waiting for a sincere apology.

520
00:37:32,210 --> 00:37:33,850
You came to the clinic and left,

521
00:37:33,950 --> 00:37:35,880
so I thought you weren't ready yet.

522
00:37:35,910 --> 00:37:38,110
"I should give him more time." That's what I told myself.

523
00:37:38,180 --> 00:37:40,480
Please calm down first.

524
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:43,550
Is it that hard for you to admit your fault?

525
00:37:43,580 --> 00:37:45,480
Is it that difficult for you to apologize?

526
00:37:46,010 --> 00:37:47,580
Supernatural beings?

527
